# The 'main' function
# - It is a special entry point
# - It runs automatically when the program starts
# - It can receive command line arguments:
#   > dinocode program.dino arg1 arg2 ...
#
# Requirements:
# - Only one can exist
# - Outside the 'main' function only can exist:
#   - Function or class declarations
#   - Static global variables (their value cannot come from function or class execution)
#
# If any of these requirements are invalidated, the program will run
# normally but the 'main' function will not execute
# the compiler assumes it is a quick script that doesn't require it.
#

name = "DinoCode ðŸ¦–"

:header
  print "--------------------------"
  print "Welcome to $name      "
  print "--------------------------"

# Will be called automatically
:main args

  header

  print "The command line arguments are: "
  for arg in args
    print arg
